1163
03:03:18,539 --> 03:03:21,801
[SPEAKER_15]: I just wanted to say a few words.

1164
03:03:22,681 --> 03:03:27,284
[SPEAKER_15]: If you did not know, this year marks the 90th anniversary of the West Medford Community Center.

1165
03:03:27,304 --> 03:03:28,344
[SPEAKER_15]: Oh, yeah.

1166
03:03:28,405 --> 03:03:30,206
[SPEAKER_15]: Applause for that.

1167
03:03:30,326 --> 03:03:30,706
[SPEAKER_15]: That's right.

1168
03:03:33,339 --> 03:03:37,921
[SPEAKER_15]: It's a testament to the enduring spirit and unwavering support of our community.

1169
03:03:38,961 --> 03:03:45,003
[SPEAKER_15]: Founded in 1935, the West Medford Community Center began as a small gathering place for black residents.

1170
03:03:45,704 --> 03:03:52,846
[SPEAKER_15]: Over the years, it has grown to the cornerstone of this community, adapting to the changing needs and expanding its services.

1171
03:03:54,067 --> 03:04:01,910
[SPEAKER_15]: This year's theme, Your Piece of the Dream, a powerful reminder of the collective effort required to achieve Dr. King's vision.

1172
03:04:06,688 --> 03:04:07,068
[SPEAKER_15]: Excuse me.

1173
03:04:07,529 --> 03:04:13,975
[SPEAKER_15]: Dr. King was indeed a powerful advocate for the empowerment of black people and fought tirelessly against racial oppression.

1174
03:04:14,616 --> 03:04:20,142
[SPEAKER_15]: Events like this are crucial in keeping Dr. King's spirit and mission alive.

1175
03:04:20,462 --> 03:04:24,846
[SPEAKER_15]: It's always inspiring when the community comes together for such meaningful events.

1176
03:04:25,587 --> 03:04:29,070
